+# Doughnut Recall Forecast Counts
+
+## Behavior
+
+Learners on the Recall page can see how many memory trackers are due in the current half-day window and how many would be included by loading the next 3, 7, and 14 days.
+
+## Acceptance Mapping
+
+- The recall API response includes forecast counts for windows `0`, `3`, `7`, and `14`.
+- Each forecast count uses the same timezone parsing, `dueindays` offset, and half-day alignment as the existing recall loading query.
+- Counts are cumulative and monotonic by window.
+- Deleted or removed memory trackers are excluded by reusing the existing active recall query.
+- Existing `dueindays` load-more calls still return the selected `toRepeat` list.
+- The done state on the Recall page shows counts on the load-more buttons without changing current-session progress or treadmill filtering.
+
+## Out Of Scope
+
+- Changing spaced repetition scheduling.
+- Reworking recall session flow, treadmill mode, or answer handling.
+- Adding new endpoints.
+
